</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E6E1DF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/umyrlinamm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Myrlina MM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#E09C5F>(4/10/01 1:42:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.winterblood.com/graphics/forumgraphics/icon_orangecool.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: General Hate Plane Questions</span><hr size=1> TAO went up to Hate last Wednesday, right after the most recent patch.  In that patch some things had changed further in Hate.  I can tell you what -we- experienced.<br>
<br>
We broke in at zone-in.  We immediately aggroed a cleric and an Ire Ghast.  No problem.  From there we started to clear the SE corner of the zone.  There are good and bad things here.  The armor mobs in the area are for Rogues and Clerics, primarily.  (We got a Cleric BP 5 min after zoning in...luck was good)<br>
<br>
Fighting in the zone-in room is a pain in the patookis, since it is a bit cramped and people like to crowd the door.  Overall, not too bad, though.  Things started getting sketchy when we decided to move to the west wall area.  Our monk (Juzhin) made sure the WW camp was cleaned up and pulled the path clear.  However, whenever we would START to move the group towards the west wall, we would have monsters drop through the ceiling on us.  Moving along...and BAM we had 2 Abhorrents, a cleric, and a Scorn Banshee right in the middle of the party.  We killed those off and scouted all around us.  We were clean.  Started to move again and WHAM more stuff.  Eventually we just ran and got away from the area to kill the interlopers.  We arrived at the West Wall.<br>
<br>
The WW camp was a pretty miserable experience, really.  We had constant problems with people getting HT from above.  (They have beefed up the HT of the Knights of Inno as well...they were killing buffed-up clerics and enchanters in one pop)  I, at first, thought that some of our members were going up the wall and getting aggroed that way, but I watched carefully and that was NOT the case.  We were having things aggroing on people who were just sitting on the floor.  Clerics and Enchanters were the primary targets of this aggro.  <br>
<br>
We had a couple things come through the floor to fight us...but that was not too bad.  We just killed them and that was that.  The aggro that really sucked was the stuff that would NOT come down...but would beat on a ranger and a shaman.  (We got to watch Ursa get beat to death by a Champion that none of us could see...there was just nothing anyone could do)  I do not intend to go to the West Wall any time in the near future.<br>
<br>
Our solution was simply to kill the boss mob that sits on the Throne in Maestro Hall and then move into there.  I REALLY recommend having a puller who knows what he is doing.  Juzhin made this happen.  It was frustrating, but it was not a raid killer, fortunately.  Once we got to camp in Maestro Hall, things went more smoothly, but were still not silk.  We had Sages of Inno aggroing on us through the ceiling there.  Thus, we were camping out and coming back in a fair number of times.  (I just wish they would come THROUGH the floor...then we could deal with the punks.)<br>
<br>
So in answer to your question:  Things still aggro through the floor.  A lot.  I wish VI would test areas before making changes live.  And if a VI official were to tell me that Hate is SUPPOSED to work that way.....I think I would have to have a long and involved discussion about what constitutes fun and what constitutes frustration.  TAO and our friends succeeded quite nicely in our raid, but I am still irritated and frustrated by the entire experience.<br>
<br>
I do not know of a purely successful method to raid Hate, but we are going back up this Thursday, so we will be trying some new ideas.<br>
<br>
Best of luck to you!!<br>
Myrlina<br>
55th level warrior of The Arcane Order <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D7CFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uleopardfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leopardfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf Reporter<br>MMDN News Editor<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/staff.gif></span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#E09C5F>(4/10/01 6:10:16 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wolf.naplesnet.com/vanguard/images/leopard.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.winterblood.com/graphics/forumgraphics/icon_orangecool.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: General Hate Plane Questions</span><hr size=1> I was at TAO's Raid and was also at a loss. I thought it was perhaps where we were actually killing and fighting the mobs that was perhaps causing the aggro from up top but later come to the conclusion someone was using an AoE spell or weapon with an AoE proc. To test this I took my raid last night to the same camp and fought all over the floor. Only once did we get HTed from above and that was because of an AoE spell cast by a chanter. <br>
<br>
As for break-in's I can give you some info. Camp the gate in room first. IF you have problems there and get wiped out drag corpses out and to the wall and up to the TOP of the wall. You will NOT AGGRO the second floor here. We did this last night for 3 hours as we kept getting AGGROED during rezzes from the first floor EVEN when we were 3/4 up the wall, so we went to the top and finished up and not once did we aggro the roof. We even FOUGHT at the top of the wall there and didn't get HT'ed or adds. I don't know if there is a roamer who was just not there at the time but he would have to be on at least a 2 hour timer to go there because we spent AT LEAST 2 hours at the top. Once you get rezzed, rebuffed, and FM go back to the gate-in house to fight. It is tight but the safest spot. And as was said earlier once you get 3 or 4 pulls out of the way your ADDS will surely be happening alot less. From there you can do two things. IF you are there farming Armor I suggest clearing the South wall all the way to the Arch or SW camp then moving there on the wall. DO NOT go higher than HALFWAY UP THE WAll as you WILL aggro the second floor once you get close to the SW corner of the zone. Now, the imps are a triggered spawn caused by a new trap. One pice of brick in the floor near the corner building by the wall if stepped on will spawn the 2 imps. They should be called wimps, not imps. You can easily deal with them, they just scare ya at first.<br>
<br>
If your agenda is Maestro however I would clear a path to him right from the gate-in house then move to the throne room from there. Will save much time and will also keep you from roaming the walls at all and aggroing the second floor. I have heard runors that if you aggro the second floor, simply camping will not clear it. I believe the Entire raid must camp and stay out till ALL ARE OUT then come back. If the monk stays FDed he will keep the aggro, then when people get back the get it from him. It is very wierd and very different. <br>
<br>
As for aggro range that is the one good change. You can almost get within spitting range and not aggro a mob on the first floor. <br>
<br>
The second floor is filled with very tough mobs who are very hard to mez and who mostly drop crappy loot. Unless you are after a specific drop from there I would avoid it all together. <br>
